Predictors of hearing aid ownership in a clinic sample

  • 1. Measures available
  • 2. Simple data cleaning
  • 3. Missing data analysis
  • 3. Missing data imputation

  • 6. Davis subgroup
  • 7. Summary

1. Measures available

back to top

List Demographics: Age, Gender, Work, Volunteer, Live alone
Physical health: General health rating, CLSA morbidity checklist, Subjective vision (loss, rating aided), Subjective hearing (loss, rating aided, rating unaided)
Hearing health: Hearing device use, Hearing device type, Tinnitus past 7 days, 15i-SSQ, Social Isolation Measure, EmoCheQ, HHIE-S, Audiogram
Cognitive health: Subjective cognitive impairment, Cognitive Self Report Questionnaire
Mobility and balance: Mobility aid use, Activities and Balance Confidence scale
Quality of life: Satisfaction With Life Scale, WHO-BREF
Mental health: Patient Health Questionnaire-4 item (PHQ-4)
Social factors: Loneliness, Social Network Index, Social Participation Frequency, Social Participation Types, Social Support (Medical Outcome Survey)
Views: Connections between hearing loss and health, Motivations for seeking hearing help


2. Simple data cleaning

back to top

Rules
  • For single-item variables (e.g.loneliness): NAs are left as is.
  • For morbidity checklist: All responses other than yes (NAs, No, Dont know) are treated as no.
  • For subjective vision or hearing loss, Dont know is recoded to NA.
  • For composite variables: If a participant has NA for all items, the composite score is also NA.
  • WHOQOL-BREF: Follow their protocol for NAs.
  • For SIM, EmoCheQ, CSRQ, PHQ4, Views on motivations: Impute case mean.
  • For 15i-SSQ: Impute case mean within subscale.
  • For HHIES: Impute case mode within subscale.
  • For ABC: Recode NAs to 0 (single participant).
  • For Social Network Index: Recode NAs to never.
  • For Social Participation: Recode NAs to never.
  • For Social Support: Recode NAs to none.
  • For Views (Connections): Drop foil item; only correct items credited.

Method for imputation

under construction

  • Use predictors that correlate 0.5 or better to impute missing data in a variable. If there are no such predictors, adjust threshold to 0.4, then 0.3, then 0.2.
  • MICE settings: total of 5 imputed datasets, with a maximum of 10 iterations per dataset, using predictive means matching to impute missing values.

7. Summary

back to top

How consistent is the effect of anxiety?

  • Having greater anxiety predicts HA ownership, in the bigger sample with mixed hearing, and in the smaller samples limited to HA candidates only

Besides anxiety, what are other consistent predictors of HA ownership?

  • The WHO-BREF question on having enough money for your needs, for all three samples
  • EmoCheQ, for HA candidates only (i.e.WHO, Davis)
  • Volunteering, in the mixed and WHO samples
  • PTA4BE, in the mixed and WHO samples
